[[File:Gol-farmer-1699.jpg|thumb|right|300 px|Bjørn Frøysåk with his family (including deceased members). Painting from 1699.]] '''Bjørn Tolleivson Frøysåk''' (1634 &ndash; 1709) was a Norwegian farmer and merchant. <ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Bjørn Tolleivson Frøysåk |first= |last= |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=http://snl.no/Bj%C3%B8rn_Tolleivson_Fr%C3%B8ys%C3%A5k |language=Norwegian|accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref>
Frøysåk was born at [[Gol, Norway|Gol]] in [[Buskerud]], Norway. He was born into one of the major farming families in [[Hallingdal]]. His father, Tolleiv Arneson Frøysåk (1605-1677),had owned several properties. Frøysåk worked as a farmer all his life. In addition to farming, Frøysåk took part in [[timber trade]] and trading of [[real estate]], and was ran a [[coaching inn]].
Frøysåk was married twice. With Ingebjørg Hersgård (died 1680), he had seven children. With Guri Tolleivsgard (1659-1733), he had eight children. Frøysåk is particularly known for a painted [[epitaph]] from 1699, showing Frøysåk with his family (both his wives including the deceased Ingebjørg and children). The epitaph, originally in [[Gol Stave Church]], was relocated to the [[Norwegian Museum of Cultural History]] in 1906.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Bjørn Frøysåk |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Torill |last=Thømt |authorlink= |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Bjørn_Frøysåk/utdypning |language=Norwegian |accessdate=25 August 2012}}</ref>
