{{Infobox newspaper | name = El Cronista | logo = | image = | caption = | type = Daily [[newspaper]] | format = | owners = | founder = Martin Giménez Antonio | publisher = | editor = | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = | political = | language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]] | ceased publication = | relaunched = | headquarters = [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] | circulation = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = 0325-5212 | oclc = | website = [http://www.cronista.com/ Cronista.com] }}
'''''El Cronista''''' (''[[Spanish language|Spanish]]: The Reporter'') is a daily business [[newspaper]] published in [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]].<ref name="clarin01">{{cite web | url=http://edant.clarin.com/diario/2000/10/21/s-05702.htm | title=La historia de un pionero (The story of a pioneer) | publisher=[[Clarín (Argentine newspaper)|Clarín]] | date=October 21, 2000 | accessdate=March 13, 2012 | quote=El Cronista fue el primer diario argentino especializado en temas económicos y financieros. (El Cronista was the first Argentine newspaper specializing in economic and financial issues.)}}</ref><ref name="businessweek01">{{cite web | url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=29291018 | title=Company Overview of El Cronista Comercial | publisher=[[Bloomberg Businessweek]] | accessdate=March 13, 2012 | quote=El Cronista Comercial is a business and financial newspaper based in Argentina.}}</ref><ref name="nyt01">{{cite web | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/06/14/business/world-business-briefing-americas-pearson-buys-argentine-daily.html?scp=1&sq=El+Cronista&st=nyt | title=WORLD BUSINESS BRIEFING: AMERICAS; PEARSON BUYS ARGENTINE DAILY | work=[[The New York Times]] | date=June 14, 2000 | accessdate=March 13, 2012 | quote=The Spanish unit of the British media company Pearson P.L.C. bought Argentine's oldest business daily, El Cronista, for an undisclosed price}}</ref><ref name="nyt02">{{cite web | url=https://www.nytimes.com/1978/06/14/archives/argentine-editor-disappears.html | title=Argentine Editor Disappears | work=[[The New York Times]] | date=June 13, 1977 | accessdate=March 13, 2012 | quote=Julian Delgado, editor of two of Argentina's leading business journals, disappeared nine days ago and has not been heard from, both papers reported last night.}}</ref>
It was founded by Martin Giménez Antonio and first published as '''''El Cronista Comercial''''' on November 1, 1908. In 1989 the name was changed to ''El Cronista''.<ref name="clarin01" />
It was the first business daily newspaper in Argentina.<ref name="clarin01" /><ref name="nyt01" /> In 1994, it was the first newspaper in Argentina to [[Online newspaper|publish online]].<ref name="clarin01" />
It is published by [[Unidad Editorial]].
