== Reception ==
''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine said, "''Life of Kylie'' is meant to show us the person behind the pout. Yet Jenner combines the self-obsession of a teenager with the reflexive crouch of someone who has learned to quash confessional impulses."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/4876992/life-of-kylie-jenner-review/|title=Kylie Jenner Struggles to Appear Real in Her New Reality Show|date=August 4, 2017|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|accessdate=August 8, 2017}}</ref> Sadie Gennis of ''[[TV Guide]]'' commented that the show "is like its star: searching for purpose, but mostly very, very sad."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/news/life-of-kylie-series-premiere-review/|title=''Life of Kylie'' Makes Me Sad|first=Sadie|last=Gennis|date=August 6, 2017|work=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=August 8, 2017}}</ref>

