{{Infobox sportsperson | name = Raymond Ocampo | image = | image_size = <!--Only for images narrower than 220 pixels.--> | alt = | caption = | headercolor = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | birth_name = | fullname = Raymond L. Ocampo, Jr. | nickname = | nationality = [[Filipino people|Filipino]]-[[American people|American]] | ethnicity = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1953|2|10}} | birth_place = [[Lubao, Pampanga]], [[Philippines]] | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|death year|death month|death day|birth year|birth month|birth day}} --> | death_place = | resting_place = | monuments = | residence = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = | years_active = | employer = | agent = | height = | weight = | spouse = | life_partner = | other_interests = | website = | country = [[Philippines]] | sport = [[Luge]] | rank = | event = | collegeteam = | universityteam = | league = | league_type = | club = | team = | turnedpro = | partner = | former_partner = | coach = | retired = | coaching = | worlds = | regionals = | nationals = | olympics = | paralympics = | highestranking = | pb = | medaltemplates = | show-medals = }} '''Raymond L. Ocampo, Jr.''' (born February 10, 1953)<ref>https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/oc/raymund-ocampo-1.html</ref> is a retired [[Filipino-American]] luger. He represented the Philippines at the [[1988 Winter Olympics]]. He participated at the Winter Olympics' [[Luge at the 1988 Winter Olympics – Men's singles|men's singles event]] where he ranked 35 out of 38 overall. His Winter Olympic stint was almost put in jeopardy due to some issues with the kind of passport he should be holding to represent the Philippines at the Olympics.<ref>{{cite web|author=Michael Janofsky |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/11/29/sports/olympic-profile-raymond-ocampo-one-man-luge-team-with-tale-of-2-flags.html |title=OLYMPIC PROFILE: RAYMOND OCAMPO; One-Man Luge Team With Tale of 2 Flags - New York Times |location=Philippines, Republic Of The; Calgary (Alberta) |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1987-11-29 |accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=MICHAEL JANOFSKY, Special to the New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1988/02/04/sports/luge-racer-at-center-of-controversy.html |title=Luge Racer at Center of Controversy - New York Times |location=Philippines, Republic Of The |publisher=Nytimes.com |date=1988-02-04 |accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref> The [[Philippine Olympic Committee]] eventually allowed him to compete under the Philippine flag without a [[Philippine passport]] despite previously requiring Ocampo the said type of passport. Ocampo previously insisted that under the rules by the [[IOC]] that he as a Filipino-American dual citizen is eligible to represent the Philippines as he did not competed for another country as a luger prior to the Olympics.<ref>{{cite news|last=Janofsky|first=Michael|title=Calgary Olympics festivities begin with the opening of villages|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1129&dat=19880206&id=28xRAAAAIBAJ&sjid=5G0DAAAAIBAJ&pg=2379,1823054|accessdate=18 February 2014|newspaper=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette|date=6 February 1988}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Lift for Calgary Pinoy|newspaper=Manila Standard|date=5 February 1988}}</ref> Ocampo first competed at the [[Empire State Games|1986 Empire State Games]]. Ocampo is also a lawyer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/1988-01-31/sports/8801070215_1_international-luge-association-winter-sports-winter-games |title=One-man Team Philippines Has Nothing To Luge - Sun Sentinel |publisher=Articles.sun-sentinel.com |date=1988-01-31 |accessdate=2014-02-10}}</ref>
Ocampo was designated as honorary captain of the national luge team of the United States at the [[2010 Winter Olympics]] in Vancouver.<ref name="americanbar1">http://www.americanbar.org/content/dam/aba/administrative/science_technology/ocampobio.authcheckdam.pdf</ref>
Ocampo is the current President and CEO of Samurai Surfer LLC, a private consulting and investment company.<ref name="americanbar1"/>
