'''John Reidar Floeng''' (15 May 1918 – 24 December 2014) was a Norwegian politician for the [[Conservative Party (Norway)|Conservative Party]].
He was born in [[Åsnes]], but moved to [[Mysen]]. He started his career in the [[Norwegian State Railways (1883–1996)|Norwegian State Railways]], but inherited his father-in-law's company Ous & Co in 1948. After thirty years as chief executive he finished his career as office manager in Lundeby & Co.<ref name=obit>{{cite news|title=Reidar Floeng|last=Unaas|first=Erik|date=9 January 2015|work=Aftenposten|page=23|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
Floeng was elected as mayor of Mysen, serving from 1952 to 1955.<ref name=obit/> He served as a deputy representative to the [[Parliament of Norway]] from [[Østfold]] during the term 1961&ndash;1965.<ref>{{Stortingetbio|JRFL}}</ref>
